{"content": "After 6 months, you can continue to get hospice care as long as the hospice\nmedical director or hospice doctor recertifies (at a face-to-face meeting) that\nyou\u2019re still terminally ill.\nYou pay:\n\u2022 Nothing for hospice care.\n\u2022 A copayment of up to $5 per prescription for outpatient drugs for pain and\nsymptom management.\n\u2022 Five percent of the Medicare-approved amount for inpatient respite care.\nOriginal Medicare will be billed for your hospice care, even if you\u2019re in a\nMedicare Advantage Plan. ", "content_type": "text", "score": null, "meta": {"_split_id": 144, "_split_overlap": [{"doc_id": "12ae24e8bccecde6f3e4afb623e6f540", "range": [0, 221]}, {"doc_id": "b0633614a399aebd8211f3630f3690dd", "range": [394, 494]}]}, "id_hash_keys": ["content"], "embedding": null, "id": "680d9d8b736283a91fb78a200f9ea19a"}